race.description: Tathra Beach Country Club Tathra Cup Handicap
race.comment: HOLY HELL (2) lightly raced mare heading in the right direction. Kept fresh when up in trip for a classy victory over 1400m at Albury. Expected to shoulder the extra weight and gets every chance from the low draw. PLAYFUL PUZZLE (6) slashing return at Gundagai first-up when a narrow second, then almost a month between runs when sixth over 1600m at Kembla Grange. Further improved now and worth noting her only win was at her third-up run. Solid top-three prospect. AMANOAH (5) model of consistency this time in and will appreciate getting out to the mile. Ran on late from back in the field when second over 1460m at Queanbeyan. Leading player proven at the trip. LOVEHUNTER (9) broke through at her eighth race start with a narrow victory over 1650m at Moruya. Stays in the calculations with Heywood retaining the ride.
